[SN]TITLE[SN]
Bolton Wanderers 4-0 Gillingham

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Bolton Wanderers thumped Gillingham to move back up to second in League One.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Gary Madine headed in Josh Vela's cross to give the Trotters the lead before Vela made it two with a composed finish from Zach Clough's backheel.
Jake Hessenthaler headed just wide for the visitors after the break.
Madine scored his second of the night with a header from Jay Spearing's free-kick before Sammy Ameobi completed the scoring after cutting inside and hammering a shot into the top corner.
